content: It's addictive. I've already spent 20 hours on it and I've barely touched the surface. Easily worth 10 bucks.

All in all I have downloaded and bought this game 5 or 6 times now, it never disappoints. Almost all of the brothers games are very well done and you can tell they put a lot of effort, heart, and story into their franchise.... This however happens to be my favorite and even though I have yet to complete the game I am sure it will take a while to unlock all of the various types of combat that is included.... Great job!!

There are some improvements I would love to see made, such as better graphics and a wider variety of weapons, but the controls are perfect and while the game does force a few decisions on you you can easily change things later with no penalties. For a game made by just two people I have to say this game is wonderful. Well worth the price, and my personal favorite of the series. The whole Star Traders series has a definite Warhammer 40,000 feel, so fans of that universe should check these out.
Deceptively deep game... just imagine if these guys would be asked to do a Warhammer 40,000 title.

From Dev testing to users feedback inspired updates, the Trese bros kill it with constant fresh content. You can count on attention to detail and classic RPG joy for the life of your device and beyond. Buy now gamers, it's a no-brainerüòé
Another superb trese game. Thanks. .

These two brothers know how to make really good games! This one is special in my opinion because after my phone completely crashed a few days ago I got a new phone and paid the cash for it again....... Growing up with Atari and the original Nintendo, Sega, Playstation these games are soooo much better. Anyway they guys are supposed to have a new game in progress that will be another masterpiece. I will always buy Templar Battleforce anytime time! Try it you won't be disappointed!

I have every Trese Bro's game available on android, and will continue to get all the new ones. They started with amazing and just keep getting better with time. I especially enjoy the way the star trader and templar game universes are the same.

True as advertised, and the best tenner you'll spend! What a delight, strategy, tactic, and character development bundled in lite world building and standard wathammer-esque fare... Good and relaxing fun with more than enough construction to keep things moving along. Replaying levels has to wait for NG+, but keep a notepad open to chart your favourite missions on the tanked up replay he second time around.
Excellent little tactical game, and like all Trese brothers games it plays well, looks good and costs very little for the full experience.

...epic battle has ended thank you, good night and farewell..... best version of warhammer 40k i have ever played on cell. :-) Played on every difficulty, played for years...still addicted. Thx TB, you are best of elite squad of war program developers.
Was awesome but since last update it won't even load
Fun, just like all their games.
Another hit, tons of depth and a great understanding of what makes a strategy game work for phones
I would like a refund. This game was not what I expected it to be.
replyContent: Google Play has an incredibly generous refund policy. The game also has a free demo you can try if you want to see if it is your type of game! Thanks for playing our title and good luck finding one that you love.

content: Worth every cent ... It would be cool to have more customizable mechs. Like different looking armor and guns justba thought but keep up the great work
Absolutely phenemonal game. Like xcom. Just with more of a rpg feel. Cant say enough good things about it.

Great value, no cash grabbing, you get a full campaign and all characters with your purchase. Writing is cheesy but fits well for bigmech space bros battling aliens. Runs smooth, mechanics are fun, visuals dated but sharp and serviceable. If you like xcom, banner saga, and long for a 40k style tactical squad game this is the best scratch for that itch on android.
Phenomenal.

I bought it because of star traders. These developers are very dedicated to produce complex games that are extremely challenging yet enjoyable. Most importantly no pay to win or ads! Buy both games from trese brothers
Pretty awesome in all aspects. I'm happy it has a good story throughout the campaign. SOLID.

Took me a little while to get into it but I'm glad I persisted. Really enjoyable game, good story so far and gameplay is great. Graphics are a little basic, but I've enjoyed it. It's not as good as xcom in my opinion, but it's along those lines.
Fantastic turn based strategy. Lots of depth. Plenty of customization. Good story. Really nothing to complain about. Worth every penny, if not more. Thanks for another great game Trese Bros.!

Excellent game, best thing since x-com UFO defense. Great turn based game and totally worth the investment. Can't wait to see what this company puts out next in this genre. If you like Tactical turn-based games, this is a good one for you.
Very rare nowadays to find such a deep and non greedy game on mobile. I never hesitate to recommend this game and company to anyone.
I love supporting these guys. Thank you for your incredible games! Star Traders was one of my favorite games on this platform, and I'm glad Templar is equally exceptional in gameplay quality.
I wish there was an option to play as the rebels in the aliens or any other faction have their own story and make it more interesting

Originally gave it a 5 but it isn't as replay friendly as it seems. Forces you to play soldier because they cost the least to field, forces you to play incinerator class because it's mandatory to progress in the story, and forces you to play engineer for obvious reasons.

I'm a good few hours into the game and having a great time with it. Beautifully realised tbs mechanics that interact with each other in interesting ways, and it's very cool to play through the lore of an earlier period of the Dune-inspired Star Traders universe. It would be nice if there were a little more variety among enemies, and music had longer loops, but those are minor quibbles for a really neatly put together game with an unlock web to make Path of Exile nervous.
Very much a "non-mobile" game in its content. With mobile UI. Perfection.

This game is absolutely phenomenal. Well worth the 10 dollars or, better yet, 5 if it's on sale. This game appears deceptively simple, but evolves very quickly. There are many different fully customizable units to use, each with their own strengths and weaknesses. The best part? FULL control over the evolution of your troops. You can decide how to build your units, tailoring them to whatever play style you may choose. This game has very quickly become one of my all time favorites.
Solid dungeon crawler without any of the useless flash or annoying pay schemes.

A very easy recommend. I have replayed XCOM on mobile to death and this is one of the few games that match up. In a certain sense, it actually offers a lot more depth. Sure, it isn't as pretty (not by a mile) but the gameplay is solid. Even the story (of generic sci-fi fare) is compelling enough that playthroughs can run for hours without my noticing. I love that you can customize characters (at least to the degree that a perpetually top-down view allows.) Well worth the premium tag.
Amazing game. These guys make the best. The big studios can't even compare. Thanks for your hard work üòò
This is one of those rare examples of virtual perfection in game design. These developers are quietly some of the best in the business.

Works very well on phone and PC. A very complete experiencing with no in-game store trying to lure your wallet astray. The asking price is more than worth it for the full experience provided. Edit: Patch support is excellent as ever.
Gr8 fun well worth it. Try it yourself. All games from Trese Brother are good, I am enjoying them.
Love it
Good tech tree gameplay can get real intense
very good üëç
üòé
A very fun game in a great setting. Dialogue can get a bit wordy and overdone at times, but the story and mechanics make up for it.
Dope rpg with perma death!

Amazing game that easily deserves a million DLs. People are definitely sleeping on this one, as well as Heroes Of Steel. Don't hesitate to pay for the full version either. One of my top 10 favorite Android games thus far without question. Anyone complaining about paying a whole $5 for such a great game are nuts. I used to pay $50+ per console or PC game as well, without complaining, and sometimes still do. Considering these games are made by independent developers, $5 is a real bargain imho!

Really cool game, this is the exact kind of tactical strategy game that I like. It has that quality of immersion and emergent story telling that's rarely able to be captured. The customization really allowed me to build my characters and get into the world. The missions were framed in the context of the story in a way that made each one feel like an extremely tense high consequence scenario that you barely survive through. I really like the whole universe at place here

In 2018, I was slowly going insane from constant acute and chronic pain from inguinal hernia repair surgery and from the pain of a blood clot in my lung. Every day was full of dread, pain, nausea, and despair. HOWEVER, I played this great game and it meant everything to me. It was fun and it distracted me from my pains for a little bit. When will the next Trese brothers game come out? Do you know how rare it is to find quality, not pay to win, premium games?
Wish the crew combat in the new star traders were modled after this instead of the darkest dungeon style it got. A true shame. But it's good, buy it anyways.
Addictive tactical turn-based strategy game. The story and graphics are dull, but the gameplay makes up for it
This is what space hulk should have been. Great turn based strategy with rpg elements
This TBS is absolutely phenomenal! It will provide many hours of enjoyment. If you're on the fence then you can try the free demo...
Love this game
Definitely one of the best turn-based strategy game I've ever played
The graphics are fine (B range) and most enemies sound identical when killed, but everything comes together for one of the better RTS games I've played, especially on mobile. Nice job!
Very tidy game from great developers. In-depth space hulk like rpg.
Good
Fantastic tactical turn based game with no overbearing micro transactions. A good game for a good price.

Interesting and fun tactical turn based game. It has themes that feel like they are inspired by Warhammer 40k's space marines without being too cheesy but manages to NOT be a scummy rng mess like space wolf.

Exactly what i was looking for. This game is a fantastic turn based strategy. It has all the elements i have been looking for in a game on my phone. Controls are easy to use and the learning curve is nice and gentle. Definately recomend this game!
Better than expected, worth the money.
Worth the price, good mechanics and an interesting world that I'm digging.
Deep and smooth gameplay and a wonderful if wordy story. Great mobile game to add to your library

Having come from the old Templar assault game 5-7 years ago, I was a bit worried that this may not live up to the nostalgia of the older game, but it is quite frankly just as good. Perhaps too good, I find myself trapped constantly going back to play. It is that good. My only complaint is that scouts tend to feel a little... fragile when scouting, which leads me to tend to leave them in the back and scout with my paladins', captain's, and berserkers' faces. Keep up the good work!

For the better part of 2 years I have combed through games trying to find something I can sink my teeth in ( metaphorically ) and this game is it. I am just at the first few missions but already I have found what I have been looking for! Paying for games is totally fine in my book because I used to have a console game system and most of those games cost around $50.00 to $60.00 dollars plus downloadable content. I do believe this is a game I have been looking for, thanks for making it!

Really happy I purchased this game. A really wonderful turn based strategy game. Another one I must be careful with because minutes easily turn into hours while playing this. Highly recommended if you enjoy games like X-Com.

The UI is too text-heavy, and the attributes/skills system is not clear enough, although interesting. Otherwise it's an amazing XCOM-like, challenging and quite long (about 50 hours of play, no kidding). Definitely worth buying.

I absolutely love this game I'm a huge fan of turn-based tactical strategy fantasy rpg's and this is definitely #1 on my list it reminds me of this old school table-top game that's also turn-based tac-strat fantasy rpg it's called, the mutant chronicles siege of the citadel, I had so much fun with that game as a kid and I even really liked the 1st game in this series templar assault rpg most definitely worth 10$ in my opinion this game is so much fun and all of the customization that you can do.
Would give 5 stars but not a fan of rng
If you are a fan of games like X-Com, squad based games, you'll find some quality hours in this game.
The best tactics game on mobile. Period.

I've grown tired of shallow, grindy, exploitative games and looked for ages for depth of gameplay on a phone. Coming from XCom, Homm, Fallout this game offers great, deep tactical combat and a research puzzle on higher difficulties. Although I don't care for that in general, the story here is surprisingly engaging, too.

This is a vast improvement on any spacehulk game ever made. The first game was excellent as well. It's a perfect example of why games workshop should not charge so much for the Warhammer patient. The whole family of games are probably the best you can get on a mobile device.
Basic/retro graphics (nice artwork though)but plenty of depth in the storyline and squad development. High replay value, if you like tactical games this is worth the money.
Finally a turn based strategy with some substance, depth of gameplay and a reasonably original story so far. One that doesn't try to force your wallet open is a rarity these days and always welcome!
Does GW better than GW does. It's a solid turn based with engaging mission design and unit options. Plays awesome on touch screen.
Only a few missions in but having a blast
It's got the Trese Brothers level of infinitely replayable gameplay with a layer of polish I've not seen in their games before. Great gameplay, looks fantastic, would rate it 6 if I could!
Buy everything they make

This game progresses at a very nice speed and has an interesting and somewhat flavorful text and story. The tech tree is fun and involved and the missions seem to have different kinds of objectives. I even just got a choice within the story to accept one of four different missions to go forward, and it was presented as a non-linear storyline.
Nice tactical game
Excellent game

A fun, challenging, rewarding game from a consistently dependable developer. I've stumbled across quite of few Trese Brothers' games now and they're all consistent in one category. A strong gameplay mechanic that rewards practice and keeps players on their toes. An honest developer that won't trick you, or your kids, into expensive IAP schemes is rare. Equally rare is having no advertising to bloat your data bill. You get what you pay for and it is always worth your money.
Awesome! This is exactly what I need in an app game, depth and tactics! Please make a second one!
Yes, very much so.
Favourite mobile game of all time
an excellent turn based strategy game
Super awesome game, keepem coming!
A great xcom-like with it's own character, rather than a rip-off of something else!
Fun turn based strategy. No microtransactions.
good

Pretty nifty rogue - like The graphics are well designed, the gameplay is simple and clever, and the XP system looks promising. I especially like the fact that it's a one - time purchase without in - app purchases. My only worry is the repetitiveness of the missions, which the storyline doesn't quite manage to alleviate. I might change my mind after I finish the campaign, though.
love it to shreds
very fun
Big improvement over templar assault. No permissions and well worth the price
Loved the permadeath mode

Surprisingly good game with real depth to the story and development of the characters. The ability to respec as you further explore the skill tree is a very nice feature. Absolutely one of the best mobile games I've played in a while.
Quality & quantity!
Fantastic game! This is my second Trese Brothers game, following Star Traders Frontiers. Deep skill tree and lots of fun tactical decision making. Early Star Traders lore is an added bonus for me.
didn't play for very long at all but it seemed well optimized, well made game that does exactly what you'd want a 40k xcom style game to do.

This game... How can i put it simply? It got everything a RPG needs: Customizations, deep skills tree, Soldier Classes, a good story and a better gameplay. If you love Tactical Rpg this is for you. I bought it when it was on sale... almost wish i paied full price for it!
This hits exactly the spot for me on tactical turn based games. Only mobile game I have ever paid for and worth every penny.
closes when I open a game please refund! thank you
replyContent: No problem! Refunds are easy and automatic on Google Play. If you need support with your unique device issues just email me I can try to help you troubleshoot whatever is wrong with your particular S9 phone. Thanks!

content: Really great game, cool story, no massive downloads, no micro transactions. This is what i want from mobile gaming
It was ok. Never have enough points to try all the character combinations. I abandoned the last level. Don't try to clear it then kill the boss. You have to do both at the same time.
Very fun sci-fi Final fantasy Tactics sequence mobile game.
A solid tactical rpg, with the kind of depth thats hard to find in phone games.
deep story and paper and pen levels of RPG customisation and tactics. not for casual gaming you've been warned
A single purchase for a whole game; that alone is rare today, but its a well made game too!
outstanding

Absolute must have. A diamond in disguise. You have to like the graphics, 
and after a while you will. But what makes this game superior is the 
execution. The well crafted tactical warfare. Choices you have to make in 
strategy, building your templars to your fitting and when it all comes 
together you have an absolute blast playing this.
One of the few enjoyable games you can get on mobile. There is a good level of variety in the equipment and talents letting you build unique soldiers.
This is, beyond a shadow of a doubt, a very good game.

You can build a unique force with requisitions, which adds a diverse layer upon the already feature-rich layers of advancement for each and every one of your templars. Set in the awesome Star Traders universe, this is indeed a core Trese Brothers installment.
A rare gem of quality amongst the sea of rubbish that is in the store these days. Feels very oldschool, which to me is great, but some might not appreciate.
it's a simple game with a surprising amount of replayability and it's a lot of fun if you like turnbased strategy.
i have not found a better built phone game before or since the story us amazing and the gameplay so much fun.
Good
This game is amazing, it would be better if the projectiles or weapons looked different but it is still absolutely amazing and is probably the second best tbs game for mobile, the first being xcom.
Absolutely worth every cent.
Game play is good and customization is is just what I was looking for.

Stellar jump in interface quality, presentation, and production on what already was a damn solid gameplay foundation. An amazingly fun strategy game perfectly optimized for mobile but with the depth of many PC based predecessors. Resource management, diverse skill trees, and well paced combat/mission structure keep things interesting and encourage multiple play styles. Trese are the Intelligent Systems/Ensemble Studios of mobile, and Templar Battleforce is without a doubt worth every penny.
Robust old school gameplay that is sorely lacking in the modern superficial games. Well worth it!
So amazing I bought it on applestore, and when I switched to Androids I happly bought it again on google play store! Alltime top 5 game...on any platform!
War hammer 40k lite. All the trappings of a space hulk game with none of the hangups of a licensed game. Fun turn based tactics.

If you think before you act, this game is for you. If you go in all guns blazing hoping for the best. You are not gojng to have fun with this game. It is a bit pricey but it is very well thougth out. Hours and hours of great fun.
I've played other games from this developer and they are the best of the best. Great gameplay. No ads. This game is a ton of fun and has awesome replay potential.
Gamesworkshop , call these guys. It's criminal they arent making wh40k games.
One of the best Strategy games on Android. It has easy to learn controls and features, but also tons of customization. Hopefully there might be an expansion or sequel in the works.
worth the 10 bucks
Turned based Action at its finest
good
Worth the money!!!
downloaded and played several years sgo. just reloaded to my new device and still an entertaining and engaging game. love the combat system , particularly overwatch. whens the new adventures coming?
Lo-fi but very fun tactical combat game set in the Trese Brothers universe inspired by 40K, Dune, and Fading Suns.
bloody awesome
Great game. Would love more content.
Great game.

This game is very challenging with vast amounts of RPG and strategy elements. The controls and graphics could use a little work. I was rushed into rating by the nagging rating reminder so it has only 4 stars. After I play a little longer I'll consider 5 stars.
Wonderful game
refreshing pure rpg experience, no in app purchases, no pay-to-win. love it

I don't often give five stars. This is a game I keep coming back to. An interesting story with a good variety of missions and as much challenge as you can handle. I would love to one day see a sequel.
Solid tactics with smart combat system and good progression variety. UI is comfortable even on small screen size. Decent plot and good writing included.
i enjoy it, it felt smooth and was a nice top down rpg. the only coplaint i had was how the enemies kept bypassing the guys on overwatch
The best turn based strategy for android...... All You need to know. Now download it and enjoy!

Good game however, playing any decent or good game on a smart phone is like eating your meal off the floor, video games belong on consoles or computers, not phones, except maybe simple games like chess or the like.
amazing
gid fun

Definitely worth the money. I have wanted to play this game for a while and im finally glad I can. Honestly Games Workshop should use this game as a template for their tactical games. This game really scratches my want to play 40k.

Xcom meets Warhammer. You have a squad of pretty much space marines fighting aliens (xenos) in turn based, grid based combat. The classes and skills are interesting and the request ion system unlocks new skills and units for even more depth. The icing on the cake are the branching story paths and the permadeth option for even more replayability. OH, and it's 100% offline, requires no permissions and can run on toasters of a phone.
Well made.

The Trese Brothers games are simply amazing. The best ones in the store. And this one is by far the best one I've played, and I have all of the others (except the last one). The depth, balance, and sheer immersion in this game blows my mind. I love you guys, please never stop making the best games ‚ù§
Immersion service at a great price. Keep up the good work :)
Great game lots of fun. Tons of options including skills and equipment. Can be a little hard to move units around on small screen but a solid game heavy inspired by warhammer.
Once again a superb game from the most conscientious developers in the app store.
One one the best indie devs around. Astounding work for two guys. Still updates after years.
Very great game...love it
One of the best mobile games I've played.

It's amazing and very strategic, I like the graphical style. I already played the predecessor on Android 2 :D Buy at whatever price it is currently offered. This is better than many so called AAA-games.
great game, solid strategy and fun classes.
Outstanding tactical RPG with an engaging story. Highly recommended!

The Warhammer 40k game I'd always wanted, but never found. The game's plot is adequate to drive my involvement, but the real genius of the offering is its customization and character development. If you're a 40K fan, don't expect a re-skinned Warhammer universe; but the game still feels a lot like home. So power up your armor, don your wargear, and check your weapons - the enemies of Man await. Those xenos aren't going to purge themselves...

Lately..... 1. I have regretfully feasted upon my loyal and much loved dog to nourish myself. 2. Because I lost my job, my family and my dignity. (and now my pet) 3. I am completely devoid of any true appreciation of reality and I no longer sleep.... BUT even the pain of starvation and the emptiness of isolation; the indignity of being destitute; the malignant torture of sleep deprivation and the incessant itching associated with parasitism capitalizing upon a complete lack of personal hygeine.... All of this is forgotten when my Ironman Captain counters a game ending death blow against a Narvidian warrior. You must own this masterpiece! Now excuse me as I sever my leg for dinner.
In depth, full flavored game play in a portable package. Hard to go wrong with a Trese Bros production.
Love it, plz make a sequel or somethin like with more classes
One of the best tactical games available. Highly recommend
This game is really well made. I love turn based, squad based tactics games and this one is top notch.
Have this on pc and mobile. Controls can be abit more fiddly on mobile due to the small screen. Otherwise a fantastic game, easily one of the top 10 games on android!

Perhaps 20 missions in on normal difficulty and I've given up. The Trese brothers, their beta testers, et al, don't understand what normal difficulty means...and the fun factor rapidly ebbs. I've been playing games (often on hardened difficulty) since the original Wolfenstein in 1992 and devs just forget that hardness does not equal fun. It's a simple, but much overlooked truth! Sadly, I'm done with these Trese games and I don't think that I'll be back...
Great turn based gameplay great mechanics. Makes me think of warhammer but without the incredible hit or miss of recent warhammer games.
Really Worth the Money, No Turn-Base strategy game is more Intense and Fun than this game! If you want some Nostalgia at your Templar Assault Experience then you should buy this. Nice Work Devs :)
Great little TBS gsme.
Easy gameplay and definite replayability. Bought this game when it was on sale but would have gladly paid full price. SO MUCH TO DO!!!
No BS turn-based offline squad-based strategy. High replayability, easy to slot in and out of playing. Still good years down the road!
Great turn based tactics game.
Fun game. Like warhammer 40k alot.
Great game, perfect for phone.
The req.-tree could have been better designed. Also less demand on pre-game map knowledge would have been nice.
Amazing and deep tactical strategy/rpg

Reminiscent of Games Workshop in design elements and lore. Tactically interesting. Upgrade options for your mechs are many, and I enjoy setting them up. Very occasionally I find the UI lacking. eg it's easy to throw a grenade at your own units. It's mostly very well thought through. Many hours of entertainment. The most expensive android game I have, and I don't regret spending.
Pretty good game with a combat style that is like secrets of mana, just what I was looking for! I will say though, the story line / character progression is lacking in excitement a little

Great tactical game for droid. Enjoyed it a lot. Though it looks like Warhammer clone, it has it's own story and good tactical turn-based battles. I can recommend this game to any fan of turn-based combat games.
Freaking awesome job.
kinda like if xcom and Warhammer had a child. This game is flawless. You will get hooked minutes.

I already loved this game. Fantastic story, strategy, and gameplay. Now they just updated the entire UI. Looks fantastic! If you like strategy gaming give this one a shot - you won't be disappointed. These devs know how to make great games and continue to support them long after release. Their entire library is worth checking out.

Clearly taking a lot of ideas from WH40k Leviathan, but this game still shines. Though it may seem pricey at $10, I have found it to be worth every cent. Game play is polished, there is tons of options for customization, and multiple paths to take to complete missions. This game is a tactics based science fiction adventure in the Star Traders universe with a rich story. I had layered Star Tarts before AMD did not get very far into it, but after playing this game I wasn't to give it another try.
Interesting sort of quests, good, I reccomend this minigame
Fun and makes you think.
Worth the $

In-depth turn-based squad tactics, slightly reminiscent of X-com, but very much distinct and unique, with a variety of well balanced gameplay options. This is a true gem, and buying it supports indie devs, who care enough about their product to provide ongoing tweaks and balances long after release. Game design at its finest, stop reading this overlong review and buy it already, dammit!

It's a great turn based strategy game, I'd give it a 4.5 if I could. I knocked a star off for random spawns. Since diagonals are a thing, parking a tank in front of a spawn point hardly slows it down if it decides to walk around him. So you can get unlucky with spawn attacks. Otherwise love it.
Oh my god... better gameplay than xcom... absolutely shell shocked by the value here. buy this
Great RPG. Keep it up.
One of thr best turn based rpgs I have found on mobile that isn't a port.
This is the sci-fi SRPG I was looking for! Fantastic game. 5 stars.
Haven't been playing on my laptop since i started playing this on my phone. Very fun and addictive.
Good
One of the few mobile games that has depth comparable to PC titles.
Excellent game built for hard core gamers and tabletop fans
Great old skool turn based RPG. Def one of the better games I've spent time w and recommend it fully.
Awesome game! Thank you!

Overall an excellent tactical turn based combat game. Really enjoying it. 
Well worth the price.

Impressive storyline and mission design. Similar to Warhammer 40K, but with 
more streamlined backstory.

Awesome game on both PC and mobile. I have nothing to add that hasn't been 
said more than a thousand times already, but if you're on the fence, check 
out the demo version here on the Play Store.
Great tactical game. Very in depth. Huge skill tree. Not pay to win.

This is a console/PC quality turn based strategy game. No crappy dumbed 
down mobile gameplay, f2p shenanigans, or ads. The only thing it's missing 
is cloud saves, everything else is 5 stars. It's just unfortunate that I 
can't play the same squad on my tablet and my phone. Also if you're looking 
at different stores to get it from go with the Google play store, or steam. 
Do not get it from the Amazon App store, it's a year behind in updates.

Great game. I've been looking for a good mobile game to fill my turn based 
strategy needs.

Could not be more pleased with this cool not so little game. A few bucks 
and some great game play. Excellent job

Brilliant. Simple and yet it comes with so much depth. Cant put it down 
after it progress to above level 6.

I had to factory reset my phone and reinstall the game and lost all 
progress! Even though I was logged in with my google ID there seems to be 
no way to restore my profile. Devs, can you help?

I prefer to pay for games rather than "free" one that end up costing a lot 
more than you first think. I prefer turn based strategy games and this one 
is one of the best I have ever played on a tablet. Complex yet easy to 
learn with time. Great graphics. Imaginative. Very happy with it.
Just what I was looking for in a turn-based strategic combat game.
Another excellent game from VERY reputable developers.

Never written a review but this game deserves it. The skill tree alone puts 
most console games to shame. Great strategic combat and leveling system. A 
lot of quality content and replay value. Fantastic developer cant wait to 
see what's next

Love this game and this developer who just keeps pumping out updates. There 
is so much depth in customization of characters and tactics. And it 
delivers immense content and replay value! In an era of microtransactions, 
this game is an oasis. To the the devs....just...thank you
replyContent: @alan - being able to change the difficulty on the new game + option is on our list to add to the game.  Looking forward to seeing it in an update, great suggestion!

content:
Great game. Perhaps the best mobile game I've played. These devs have done 
well. You won't regret your purchase.
Amazing turn based strategy game. Must have for any fans of Space Hulk.

Great turn based combat strategy allowing choices of improvement to units 
as they progress.
Excellent! Just buy it.
If I didn't love this game, I'd be a Heretic

One of the best Trese Bros games. Good gameplay, good balance, good art,

This game is terrible.  It starts off okay at best, the classes give you 0 idea what you're doing, none of the mechanics are adequately explained, and worst of all it's just punishing in extremely unfair, unlikable ways. One second the enemies require a spawn point, next second their spawning ALL OVER the areas you just cleared out. The abilities make no sense, and worst of all there's no system for you to learn what a soldier can do during a game, WHICH IS KIND OF IMPORTANT considering many of the abilities have limited uses. Even worse, they make no sense, an ability with MASSIVE range can just not do anything, attacks that "hit multiple units" do not do that, and the game uses RNG in the worst possible places.   And screw the mission lengths too, this is mobile, yet some of these missions EASILY require 45+ minutes to beat and you can't save mid game, you HAVE to finish or go back.   If you're a masochist who's bad with money, you might like this game. If you like your games having even the tiniest amount of approachability, get the hell away NOW.

Deep strategy game, unlike anything else on the mobile platform. In this game you command every action for a team of soldiers in mechanical suits called Leviathans. Turn based combat with multiple class types. Now what really set this game apart and makes it a deep experience is the deep level of balance and polish this game has received.  Many updates with fan suggested balance and changes, not to mention Dev experience with making games mean the UI is finely tuned for a mobile experience. Another importand part of this game I wanna point out is  tree of unlocks which is HUGE, this is where you unlock new equipment, gear, talents each class has access to but new classes as well. This tree is very well balanced which I find rare in many mobile games, with such a large variety of options you are really given a lot of freedom to build your Battleforce the way your want. for example right now I have Paladins which are a sword and board class which can heal, so a melee medic, and the Hydra which is a aoe flame based class. With these two and the standard Soldier class which specialize in overwatch commands I'm able to play in an agressive playsyle that let's me clear, advance, and hold while progressing thugh each map.  Just the way I want to, but could easily pick some dual wield Berserker class unlocks and make mincemeat out of anything that gets in your way, or snipe from afar with tree unlocks that give your scouts access to powerful rifles and talents which increase the damage they put out. And more, so much more this game is fantastic, it's challenging, it's well balanced, and most of all it's fun.

Trese bros games all have free demo versions, you've probably played some. You probably found some rough edges that put you off the game a one way or another.  This one has rounded off most of those jagged bits and is a complete package.  The game is a bit like Space Hulk but much much better. (Your soldiers are reasonably competent). You go on a variety of missions and your job is to be awesome at turn based tactics.   You can customise your troops in a wide variety of ways which keeps things interesting. One thing I would have liked would be for a bit of randomisation in the characters to give them a sense of true uniqueness.  Listen, it's a great game.

I've held off and held off writing a review for Templar Battleforce for a long time. The reason is that I wanted to experience most of the campaign, but I found myself loving the higher difficulty levels with Iron-man enabled. This mean't that I kept getting crushed at various points and kept starting again.   This is where I think I can now safely provide a review, at least from my perspective. The fact that I couldn't wait to make a fresh start each time and still felt as though the tactical choices presented every game were still fresh and relevant is the highest accolade I can give to any game. I've never felt the need to 'tone'down the difficulty just so I could see the rest of the story and content. I just enjoy those tactical situations so much.  So, all that said. This game is inspired by games like Space Hulk. But they have created their own universe and fleshed it out enough to make it stand out on its own. By 'they' I mean the Trese Brothers who have done another amazing job of bringing PC level complexity to mobile devices. If you like squad based tactics with unit progression done right, then Templar Battleforce is for you. No IAP's, constant development and improvement, what's not to love. Believe the 4.9 rating here, this is the real deal and worth every penny!

IN BRIEF:  An excellent call back to RTS shooters and a superb squad/tactical war game.   THE GOOD:   Fast-paced action.  Better graphics and music than the original Templar Assault.  Intriguing mission design. Each series of missions has a unique challenge.  Lower difficulties are forgiving in that they will restore all fallen templars at the end of the mission. A large research tree with few pitfalls; you have the freedom to customize a force to your playstyle, exactly as it says on the tin.    IMPROVEMENTS FROM TEMPLAR ASSAULT (the previous game) :  Facing is no longer an issue.  Ammo is now infinite, which is important since you face infinite enemies.  Mid-level resupply.  No need to buy equipment, or sell it ;; if you have researched it on the requisition tree, you can use it IF your squad member is able to handle it at all.   CONS:    Main campaign is somewhat short, only five or so campaigns. Replayability comes from repeating the same campaign at a higher difficulty level.  Tech tree is somewhat confusing. Tutorial mission 3 is as hard as later game missions, and may be a stumbling block for new players.

I will try to see if there is a way we can make some of the gear change the mech skin without breaking the bank. We're a team of two with a $0 budget, so sometimes we had to make some tough design choices!

content: At first, I was wondering why the Trese brothers decided to charge so much for their new game. I decided to buy it because of their previous track record and I'm very glad I did. This is a fantastic and engaging TBS game that really does a great job of sucking you in. There are a lot of things to unlock: armour, weapons, even abilities. I'm only on the fifth scenario, but I'm already taking my role as a Templar commander way too seriously. Buy this game right now, for Shalun!

Trese Brothers games are awesome, as always.  This one is a sci-fi version with the heroes of steel tactical combat feel (without all the walking around), set in the Star Traders universe.  Looks to be the best game yet, in a series that already stood head and shoulders above the rest.
Don't usually play this type of game, but I gave this a shot and it sucked me right in.  This is an awesome game.  It is definitely worth a try.  I don't think you'll be disappointed.

Plays like a fast paced space hulk, with a deep sense of progression and customization. Surprisingly, it works well on the phone-- frequent auto saves let you play a turn at a time. There's an actual story (!), and some good variety to the missions, with secondary objectives. My biggest complaint is that the double-tap to move is finicky, and often will slightly move the screen instead. If you enjoy squad-based tactical games, this is worth it even at full price.

At first i was hesitant because of the 2d view, but the graphics are nice once you're into the game and more detailed than it seems in screenshots.  Lots of levelling up of your templars. Solid gameplay and controls.  Worth it for rpg/strategy fans.
Great fun and another great example of Trese brothers design. Hard, but you feel you can win if you change your tactics after getting eaten alive.
Reminds me of space hulk on Playstation. Great storyline, hope you update it with firefight or some form of free play missions (non campaign mode)
Man, this game is great. Constantly updated, great diversity, and some really tense tactical combat. Definitely worth the money!
So addicting! Solid game play. Has you hooked and wanting more. *suggestion* Needs more armor colors and maybe a few armor variation choices. Apart from that, no other complaints from this guy!
Star Traders was my first Android game years ago, and most Trese games since have been awesome.  this is no exception.

The game is very good, and must have 4 ppl who liked previos game - Templar Assault. Unfortunatly it has problem with UI (galaxy Note 5) - screen tapping often doesnt work. May be tap area around unit is too small, or may be game loop is unresponsive. It's annoying and prevent 5 star review :(
Very good game got me glue to the game for hours
Ties nicely into the Star Traders lore. Worthy successor of Templar Assault.
you're working too hard on this game, i gotta check the patch every 3 days. unplayable 5/5
Best I've played to date and worth every penny. (I'm a very reluctant spender and not star trigger happy). Having played their games in the past their depth and general attitude is a general winner.
Fun and strategic,  can't get enough!
Great job, this is what I was looking for. Amazing amount of work and diversity in this game.
Good to see the developers of Trese Games, growing in skill and game sophistication. Also pleased the user interfaces are more accessible. Love turn-based rpg's, and this one is no exception.

Ignore the graphics. The amount of detail and thought that went into the game is apparent after the first mission. Tactically great with tough decisions. Always updating itself. This is what a good game should play like.

This game has you at a huge disadvantage at every turn and some of the levels are absolutely absurd. This game  is probably one of the most  horribly set up games when it comes to any sense of fair in combat. With this said it also is one of the best turn based games I have seen via app it has tremendous potential and is over all impressive. Just please give a player at least one upper hand fire power, reduction to over heating, more  direction for some levels, higher unit cap, even lower the cost of meds in the unit spawner any one of these changes and I'll rate it five out of five. Over watch isn't that much of an upper hand.
replyContent: @Willson - thanks for the feedback!  What difficulty are you playing?  Difficulty effects monster level, spawning rates, the amount of Supply Points you get--everything.  We'd highly recommend playing on Normal. Check out YouTube for great Let's Play videos to get some strategy tips. Use Overwatch, that is the upper hand in every way you've asked.

content: You get what you pay for,  a compelling game with content updated on a regular basis. No pay to win,  just you and the game.
Love the tactics

First off, I love RPG games and this one certainly lives up to my standards: turn-based, stats, rare equips and strategy. There's a lot of content available, including a deep story, a deep requisition tree for specialized paths start growth and mechanics not seen in other games. The graphics are VERY appealing. In fact, I didn't get the other Templar game because the graphics were offputting. In short, wonderful game and worth checking out.
Very good tactical rpg game.
It is worth the price, beating levels against hilarious odds is satisfying, skills all have useful benifits, and the classes are all fun to play with.
Started with 4 stars. The more I play, the more I realize the genius of this game. 5 stars.....
replyContent: Thank you for leaving a Review! We're always available to help if you have any issues, just email me at cory@tresebrothers.com and thanks for playing.

content: Title says it all. Support these guys they are very skilled at what they do!

Templar Assault was a good homage to tactical games of yesteryear, but with this the Trese Brothers show they have what it takes to expand the vision. Certainly it does borrow a lot from Heroes of Steel, another TB hit, most likely due to sharing the same engine but since HoS was solid I see no need to rate this game any less. =) No real negatives, the occasional typo will likely be fixed as soon as people flag them and my usual grumble with TB games, the repetitive music, is lot less annoying as Battleforce has multiple cues to play. I'd still like to have a more defined score of 4-5min tracks, but they're certainly improving and again, this isn't a critical issue. Waiting to see what they do with Star Traders 2 and possibly a Cyber Knights sequel! =)
replyContent: Oh boy, a Cyber Knights sequel would be fun! If you have any issues with Templar Battleforce, feel free to e-mail me at cory@tresebrothers.com

content: while I know trese games don't disappoint, i'm surprised that i'm significantly more addicted to this than any other game they made.  great tactical gameplay with rpg and deep customization elements: can't wait for the next update.
Seems very good. Couldn't enjoy the previous games because of gfx. Thumbs up for this! Not regreting buying.
So much leveling such a huge skill tree so much room for activities!

This game has it all: overwatch, skill trees, customizable marines, quasi religious overtones. Very well put together, don't let the simplistic screenshots fool you this game has as much tactical nuance as Shadowrun or FF Tactics.

Excellent game! I love all the Trese titles but this is a genuine step up. Essentially it is an installment of Templar Assault but the experience is much more immersive and story driven. Loving the new interface, the animation and faster pace of movement and combat. Looking forward even more now to Star Traders 2, and the next Cyber Knights whenever that happens. I am guessing from past games that we can count on Team Trese to keep it fresh with new updates too. Station!
Purchased this purely to support devs making quality games with no IAPs. Keep it up guys!
Their usual superior product.
Their best and most polished game so far. I would buy it again if my tablet got wiped or something crazy.
Love all your guys titles.  What happen to the cyber punk one?  Excellent work kept it up
Take X-Com and stick a Warhammer 40k skin on it. Add an engaging story, lots of customisation and hours of game play. You've got yourselves a winner.
Just needs backup support
replyContent: Kevin -- we are hard at work on adding cloud backup support! Thanks for playing.

content: Best strategy RPG Ive played on mobile. Plays like a really good old console game.
Have played a few of their games but this features better interface, graphics and sound as well as good gameplay that makes this the best of the lot.
Great tactical game. Loads of strategy.
Awesome addicting time killer
If you like their other games you will love this one.
Excellent game one again by the Trese brothers
Worth the purchase price.
Great title, from a great dev. team. I am yet to be disappointed by games from these guys
Like Xcom, but with the Trese original setting and an interesting array of tactical options.
Excellent.
Great game! Gets tough though....
Lots of fun!
Love it!
Well made, branching story points, pretty clean Ui and mechanics, lots of things to uncover and learn.  Fun times.
Only comment is that i wish the direction you were attacked from mattered like in previous games. Otherwise a ton of fun
Solid graphics, challenging deep game play - this one has it all!
For the cost of a qdoba burrito you get endless entertainment
Really lost track of the time playing this game. Thanks. I'll write you after I lose my job, my children abandons me and my wife divorces me. It's a quantum leap over TA.
replyContent: Glad you're enjoying. Don't forget to take a break and play some Star Traders ... I mean go to work and stuff. Please don't hesitate to e-mail me at cory@tresebrothers.com if you have any issues!

content: It s really a great rpg
Really great strategy game, with depth and delightfully tense battles. I didn't finish it yet, but what I experienced so far is well worth it. Great job guys.
replyContent: After you do finish the campaign, you can restart and play through again against tougher enemies and smarter AI. If you have any issues  e-mail me at cory@tresebrothers.com

content: I've been looking for something even remotely as good as xcom for some time, this is easisy up thereby . It may even be better. Excellent, challenging, tactical game play alongside a grest levelling and gear system. One thing I particularly love is the ability to respec your characters as you progress at no cost, allowing you to try your new talents and change way you play dynamically. Pure genius. The Trese brothers have absolutely smashed it with this. Any chance of cloud saves though?
replyContent: We are working on a cross-platform cloud save feature, but it is going to take me some time to finish it. If you have suggestions feel free to email me at cory@tresebrothers.com

content: Game over man! Game over...foul xenos swarm through your defence and overwhelm your heroic Templars. This bug stomp mission has gone south - time to start again, this time more Napalm!!!! Great game with a deep storyline carried over from the other titles in this series. With no advertising or DLCs this game is well worth the price of 2 Vanilla Latte's. Cheers to the developers.
replyContent: Cheers to you, Dan! Thanks for your recommendation -- and the suggestion for more Napalm! If you have any problems email me at cory@tresebrothers.com

content: Great game in many ways even superior to the space hulk games released on mobile or pc. But with more humble graphics yet superior gameplay and campaign. I just wish there was a way to replay old missions to grind a bit of RP. Also I hope the plan to add more content like campaign expansions. All in all.l, outstanding game.
replyContent: When you complete the Campaign, you will have the chance to replay it from the beginning, gain more RP/XP and take different branches if you'd like.

content: I loved the original, this build on it without ruining what made Templar Assault fun. Same basic game with a great new look and much deeper mechanics. Trese Bros are my favorite developers on mobile, this game is a premier example of why.
replyContent: Thanks for your Review, Glendon! If you're familiar with our other titles, you know we have a lot of updates planned for Templar Battleforce. If you have any issues email me at cory@tresebrothers.com

content: Ive played a few Trese brothers games in the past. They held my attention for a few hours but i often got bored. This game, however, does everything right. 8 massive classes, an epic storyline, frantic and fun turn-based strategy, deep character builds and loadouts, skill trees, interesting maps, endless replayability. If you like games like xcom and the original fallout series, this game is for you. Sure it's a little pricey, but unlike the freemium crap out there, these guys know how to make a REAL game.

Excellent game with tons of choices and a deep intriguing storyline. This is actually my second Tresse Brother's game purchased (after Star Traders RPG) and I have been impressed with both. Yes it is a tad expensive, but I feel that I made a very good purchae and I have only played the first two missions. Excited to see what the game has in store for me.
Great class system, great story, awesome combat! Overwatch is super powered on normal mode. I recommend hard mode for avid tactical strategy players!

After the updates the game went from perfect to flawless 5‚òÜ, EDIT: these are the best most responsive developers, I asked questions and they answer super fast, cloud save is being worked on!! Thanks for the heads up!!
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback and review. We are working on Cloud Save!

content: Complex round strategy with tense battles, rpg elements, a tech tree and a nice story. One of the best games for android. I hope your games keep evolving though, with new interesting gameplay elements. Greetings from blaa
Great game
A thorough and addictive game with great devs. An excellent choice for any tactical fans.

This game is very awesome with its fully customisable characters, immersive missions and nice graphics. I find myself yelling at my phone when xenos appear from nowhere :) It also expanded a lot on the star traders lore which makes the game way more enjoyable.                           If you are a fan of strategy games, I highly recommend you get Templar Battleforce, you won't regret it!!
Loved templar asault, love this even more. Is it possible to replay missions like in the 1st one? If so how?
replyContent: @Riley - welcome to the team, veteran!  Great to have Templar Assault players on board.  There is no option to directly replay a mission, but when you beat the campaign, you can replay the entire campaign with the same squad. We are hard at work adding more levels and some skirmishes you can play at the end of the campaign.

content: I love srpg and this is a great example of that. Customization, tactics, varied level design, combinations between classes, and ultimately a challenging strategy experience. I liked space hulk, but I like this more. The system works and after more than 2 days playing non stop I'm still tweaking my loadout and playing with different things. Buy this game if you like strategy and/or rpg. Only complaint is that there isn't an entry in the help section for what parry is.
replyContent: @Tom - sorry for the lack of details on that.  We will work on adding that to the game.  For now, you can check out this full combat guide we published to Steam for any answers you seek - http://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=522600159

content: Really enjoying this game so far, lots more depth and much easier to use.
Only played a few hours, but so far it's amazing.
Best Trese brothers game to date.  If you like turn based strategy RPG's, don't hesitate on this one.

How many years have passed since Templar Assault? Too many! But here we stand at the gates of it's successor...bring on the Battleforce!  The first thing I noticed was the *massive* improvements to the GFX and sound!  The sheer depth is amazing, from mission structure to the detailed customisation and the epic tech tree!.  TB have also nailed another solid chapter in the whole Star Traders saga with the story.  Nothing comes close to TBF on Android, nothing!  TBF demonstrates how you can have an undiluted turn-based strategy game on a phone, this is not a sequel for sequel sake, TBF is an object lesson on how to take a solid game (Templar Assault) and improve it in every way possible! If you loved TA as much as me, just wait until you dive into TBF! The Android strategy game of the year is here!  Perfect balance of gameplay and control via an intuitive touch screen controls. If you enjoy XCOM or even the original Space Hulk/W40K, DO NOT miss Templar Battleforce!
replyContent: Feel free to e-mail me at cory.trese@gmail.com for support at any time -- I am always available to help our players.

content: Overhead Squad Tactical Grid Scenario Combat Game with some twists and a unique approach to progression. Fight as a Templar Captain in part of the Star Traders universe taking flavor from Dune, Space Hulk, and some Hindu.¬† PRO: Simple and challenging combat that is easy to pickup and play. Lots of scenarios, varied difficulty settings, and an ever growing list of content (due to updates) help give the game long legs and high replayability. Great overwatch mechanic that is tactical without destroying balance. The devs are very involved and receptive to community feedback and the game is always improving as a result. CON: Characters could use some more customization to make each member feel more like your own. Very little game options to tailor your preferences. Music and sound effects are serviceable but could still be better, particularly music loops could be longer and more varied. Some enemy spawn locations are hard to make out leading to frustrating moments. Many levels require a "core" set of classes and don't leave much room to experiment with the less used classes. Edit: Devs have added a swap out member mechanic which does help this a bit.
Hard as nails- in a good way.

Best turned based strategy on android. Nice story with an incredibly vast setting from the other games to back it up. Units will grow if you keep them alive trough missions and you will grow fond of some of your best soldiers. Respeccing for free makes it so you can't screw up your game by freely trying new tactics. The heat system is awsome and rewards clever switching for fresh soldiers and daring self sacrifice at times. This game rocks.

From the particles of sand in the main menu blowing past a breathing Templar to the pulsating sun, the game screams polish right at presentation. The GUI is heavily borrowed from Heroes of Steel, which eschews the traditional menu blocks for detailed buttons and backgrounds of talents, used to rip enemies to pieces at the expense of both Action and Movement Points, used both to act and to move. Challenging but not unfair. Well worth $6.99 and then some! (Will have full review on star traders forum boards!).
Another hit from the Trese Bros. Nailed it again.

Greetings from the Kingdom of Derail. I have stepped forth to recommend this latest game from the Trese Brothers. The sequel to their classic Templar Assault, this game makes leaps and bounds in fun and playability. Set in their classic StarTraders Universe. The game put you in command of a large squad of Templar Knights. As you progress and gain levels, you'll be able to equip better armor and weapons. With several different classes to choose from. The combination of squads and tactics means there will be hours of game play for you have fun with. One of the coolest features of the game is taken from the lore about the Templars. With their genetic memory, they can call upon their ancestors training and reapply their Attributes, Skills, and Talents any time they want. You'll never have to feel locked into a certain path or like you've made the wrong choice in leveling up your characters. The amount of Talent and weapons combos alone will keep you busy for hours trying out all sort of great tactics and play styles. Don't forget to stop over at the TB's forum also. Get help from the brothers themselves and the thriving community of players there.

Hmm lets see. No IAPs check. No permissions required check. Complete game i buy it i own it check. Game designers are attentive to game needs check. Game is fun, challenging, and replayable check. Well what are you waiting for. Buy it now before the price goes up. As a matter of fact buy all their games. I did

Game play is incredible! You can respecilize your skills , so if you play and decide you want to change things around you do not have to start over (something I do a LOT) the story so far is great and the graphics and game play are perfect. Also you can customize how your templar look (and even the name) will write a better review later but I am at level two and want to play more. But so far this game is everything I ha e wanted and more, well worth the wait and more then worth the price!

I have been playing this game on Steam and I am so happy to have it on my phone finally. Endless reply, tons of difficulty settings and 800+ items in the tech tree. Developer is even offering a big launch discount. Buy. It. Now.
